  <!-- Section: Application Process -->
  <section id="application" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Process</h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      Korean investor visa applications require careful documentation and often benefit from professional immigration assistance. Processing times vary by visa type and application completeness.
    </p>

    <ComparisonTable columns={timelineColumns} rows={timelineRows} />

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-8 mb-3">D-8 Investment Visa Process</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Business Planning</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Develop viable business plan for Korean market. Identify industry, structure, and investment amount. Consider using immigration lawyer or consultant for guidance on visa-compatible business structures.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Company Registration</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Register Korean corporation (주식회사 or 유한회사). Deposit KRW 100M+ paid-in capital. Open Korean bank account. Register with tax office. Process takes 2-4 weeks with professional assistance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Application</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Apply at Korean embassy/consulate (abroad) or Immigration (in Korea on valid status). Submit: business registration, bank statements proving investment, business plan, passport, photos, application forms. Processing: 4-8 weeks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Visa Issuance & Entry</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Receive D-8 visa stamp (single entry) or Certificate of Visa Issuance (for consulate pickup). Enter Korea and register at Immigration within 90 days for Alien Registration Card (ARC).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Post-Arrival Setup</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Complete Alien Registration within 90 days. Obtain ARC (required for banking, phone, etc.). Enroll in NHI after 6 months. Set up business operations. D-8 is initially 1-2 years, renewable with ongoing business activity.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">F-5 Investor PR Process</h3>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Make Qualifying Investment</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Invest KRW 300M in approved assets: government bonds, approved stocks, or business investment. Must be verifiable and maintained. Real estate route (F-5-6) requires KRW 500M-1.5B property purchase in designated areas.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Gather Documentation</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Investment verification documents, bank statements, property registration (if applicable), criminal background check, health examination, Korean residence history (if converting from other visa).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Apply at Immigration</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">Submit application at Korean Immigration office. Interview may be required. Processing: 2-4 months for thorough investment verification. Ministry of Justice makes final determination.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-green-600 text-white rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Receive F-5 Status</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600">F-5 is permanent residence—no expiration. Must apply for re-entry permit (2 years) if leaving Korea for extended periods. Can work for any employer or self-employ. Eligible for citizenship after 5 years.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-6">
      <p class="text-blue-800">
        <strong>Professional help recommended:</strong> Korean immigration law is complex and documentation requirements are strict. Immigration lawyers or consultants (행정사) can navigate the system, ensure proper documentation, and communicate with Immigration in Korean. Budget KRW 3-5M for professional assistance—often saves time and prevents rejection.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

